# TypeScript Type Patterns

## Type Definitions

### Component Props

Define component props in separate `types.ts` file:

```typescript
export interface ComponentProps extends React.HTMLProps<HTMLDivElement> {
  /** React children */
  children?: React.ReactNode
  /** Classes */
  className?: string
  /** Description of prop */
  propName?: string
}
```

### Generic Types

Use generics for reusable types:

```typescript
export interface FormProps<FormValues extends FieldValues> {
  defaultValues?: DefaultValues<FormValues>
  methods?: UseFormReturn<FormValues, any, undefined>
}
```

## Type Organization

- Place types in `types.ts` files co-located with components
- Use `@/constants/types/*` for shared types
- Group related types in the same file

## Interface vs Type

- Prefer `interface` for object shapes
- Use `type` for unions, intersections, or computed types

## API Types

Define API-related types in `@/constants/types/api.ts`:

```typescript
export interface ApiResponse<T> {
  success: boolean
  data?: T
  error?: string
  details?: string
}
```

## Database Model Types

- Sequelize models extend `Model` class
- Use `Optional<>` from Sequelize for creation attributes
- Define public properties with proper types

## Type Exports

- Export types/interfaces individually
- Use named exports for types
- Group related exports together

## JSDoc for Types

Document complex types:

```typescript
/**
 * Represents the state of the modal system.
 */
export interface ModalState {
  /**
   * List of all opened modals.
   */
  listOfOpenModals: Partial<OpenedModal>
}
```
